Russian President Vladimir Poetin has signed a law imposing administrative responsibility for the infringement of the time and manner of payment of goods (work, services) in the conduct of public and municipal purchases.
The Act is intended to address the very acute problem of failure of employers to perform their duties in public and municipal purchases.
Two years ago, the situation where employers were unable to obtain payment under already executed State and municipal contracts was widespread.
At the same time, the Russian President had instructed the Office of the Public Prosecutor of the Russian Federation to take over the problem for special control.
Because businessmen themselves could not cope with unscrupulous employers who had entered into unfinished contracts, tried to avoid their payment and included illegal terms in the contract.
The problem was systemic in the country as a whole.
Since 2015, in order to protect the rights of employers to be paid on public orders, the prosecutor ' s office has submitted  9.7 thousand complaints, resulting in disciplinary proceedings against 4,500 officials and administrative 533 officials, and 75 cases have been submitted to the investigating bodies for the purpose of conducting inquiries, 46 of which have led to criminal proceedings.
As a result, more than 66 billion roubles of business debt were paid.
These huge sums have not been accumulated as a result of the failure to pay multi-billion dollars.
Many, systematic delays in the payment of services to employers for much more modest amounts have led to huge debt.
Here's a case.
The manager of a small company won a competition for social transport services for several million roubles.
The man had invested all his working capital, fully complied with his obligation, but had not received the money on time.
The result is an increasing financial coma of wages, taxes, credit that would have led to a bankrupt business if the businessman hadn't requested help from the prosecutor's office.
The problem has now been maximized in a number of regions.
However, as of the first half of the year of 2017, the total amount of debt on State and municipal contracts, as determined by the prosecutors of the entities of the Russian Federation, was about 27.4 billion roubles.
In regions where debt indicators continue to reach critical values, the prosecutor's office is operating under the manual crisis management regime.
The Attorney-General personally holds retreats with the local authorities, at which all prosecutorial failures and measures to address them immediately are examined.
Such operational meetings have already taken place this year in Jaroslavla and Yekaterinburg.
The implementation of Federal Act No. 189-FZ on the introduction of changes to the Code of administrative offences in order to establish the administrative responsibility of the employer's officials for breaching the time and manner of payment of goods (work, services) in the conduct of public and municipal purchases, signed last week by the President of the Russian Federation.
The draft law was drawn up by the Ministry of Economic Development of Russia on the initiative of the Office of the Public Prosecutor.
The new law will supplement the Code of Administrative Offences with an article which provides for a fine of 30,000 to 50,000 roubles for breaching the employer's time and manner of payment of goods, jobs and services in public and municipal purchases.
If an official had already been administratively punished for a similar offence, he would be disqualified for a period of between one and two years.
All prosecutors of entities of the Russian Federation have already been instructed to ensure that these legal innovations are applied in practice.
