In Ukraine, an offer was made to send a Russian to prison for illegal border crossing
A bill has been registered in the Verkhovna Rada of Ukraine which provides that Russians may be subject to criminal penalties for illegal crossing of the Ukrainian border.
As RT broadcasts, a document registered in the Ukrainian Parliament's electronic database suggests a three-year prison sentence for Russian citizens attempting to enter the country illegally.
It is observed that for a repeat offence or an act committed by a group of persons the sentence may be increased to five years.
If the perpetrator had been arrested at the border with a weapon, the time spent in custody would be eight years.
It was previously reported that Ukrainian border guards had apprehended Ukrainians attempting to enter Russia outside the specified crossing points.
